==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pumpkin
<hw>Pump"kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For older
<ets>pompion</ets>, <ets>pompon</ets>, OF. <ets>pompon</ets>, L.
<ets>pepo</ets>, <ets>peponis</ets>, Gr. <?/, properly, cooked by the
sun, ripe, mellow; -- so called because not eaten till ripe. Cf.
<er>Cook</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A well-known
trailing plant (<spn>Cucurbita pepo</spn>) and its fruit, -- used for
cooking and for feeding stock; a pompion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pumpkin seed</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The flattish
oval seed of the pumpkin</cd>. <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>The
common pondfish.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pumy</ent>⟦br⟧
